Citation.sTitle: Densities, Viscosities, Speeds of Sound, and Refractive Indices of Binary Mixtures of 2-Octanol with Chlorobenzenes
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, n, viscosities, c, speeds of sound, u, and refractive indices, nD, of binary liquidmixtures of 2-octanol with 1,2-dichlorobenzene, 1,3-dichlorobenzene, and 1,2,4-trichlorobenzene have been measured over the entire range of composition at 298.15 K, 303.15 K, and 308.15K and at atmospheric pressure. From the experimental data of the density, speed of sound, viscosity, and refractive index, the values of the excess molar volume, VE, deviations in isentropic compressibility, eS, and deviations in molar refraction, R have been calculated. The calculated excess and deviation functions have been analyzed in terms of molecular interactions and structural effects.
